name: Cag-dev
tagline: A machine-corrected version of the Commentaria in Aristotelem Graeca.
body:
#Welcome to **cag-dev**!

##About
This repository hosts digital versions of the _Commentaria in Aristotelem Graeca_ (CAG).

These XML files were produced by data entry company [DDD](http://www.digitaldividedata.org/), who OCR'd, corrected and encoded each volume of CAG in accordance with the latest [EpiDoc](http://sourceforge.net/p/epidoc/wiki/Home/) standards.
While adequate, more can and should be done to improve the XML (the -dev(elopment) suffix indicates the repository is open to improvement).

##Volumes

* [Vol. 1.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_1_1.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis metaphysica commentaria_ (1891) ed. Michael Hayduck.
* [Vol. 1.2](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_1_2.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis metaphysica commentaria_ (1891) ed. Michael Hayduck.
* [Vol. 2.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_2_1.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis analyticorum priorum librum 1 commentarium_ (1883) ed. Max Wallies.
* [Vol. 2.3](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_2_3.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _Quod fertur in Aristotelis sophisticos elenchos commentarium_ (1898) ed. Max Wallies.
* [Vol. 3.1](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_3_1.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In librum de sensu commentarium_ (1901) ed. Paul Wendland.
* [Vol. 3.2](https://github.com/OpenGreekAndLatin/cag-dev/blob/master/commentaria_3_2.xml): Alexander Aphrodisiensis, _In Aristotelis metereologicorum libros commentarium_ (1899) ed. Michael Hayduck.
